# Windsurf Instructions

## Project Summary

This project contains static HTML pages that will later serve as references for WordPress theme development.

The primary objective is to clean up, standardize, and improve consistency across all pages while preserving the intended design and functionality.

## Development Guidelines

### Code Quality

* Write clean, readable, and concise code.
* Prefer simple and maintainable solutions.
* Remove unnecessary complexity, duplication, and inconsistencies where appropriate.
* Keep formatting consistent throughout the project.

### Standardization

* Standardize markup, structure, naming, and organization across pages where appropriate.
* Maintain consistency in reusable sections and components.
* Improve code quality without changing the intended appearance or behavior.
* When multiple approaches exist in the project, favor a single consistent pattern.

### Changes

* Only make changes that support the requested task.
* Do not introduce new features unless explicitly requested.
* Do not make unrelated modifications.
* Preserve existing functionality and design unless instructed otherwise.

### Project Standards

* Follow existing project conventions where they are already consistent.
* When inconsistencies are found, standardize them using the most appropriate pattern already present in the project.
* Keep code organized, easy to understand, and easy to maintain.

### Before Completing Work

* Verify that pages remain visually and functionally consistent.
* Confirm that changes align with the project's standardization goals.
* Remove unused, redundant, or unnecessary code when relevant to the task.
* Keep all changes focused, deliberate, and production-ready.
